Vault user {{user}} retrieved the password of {{numOfAccounts}} accounts from CyberArk PAS after being inactive for more than {{inactiveDays}} days.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.ACTIVE_DORMANT.RECOMMEN: Make sure that this Vault user is active, and if not, consider limiting the user's access.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.AGGREGATIVE_ICE.SUBTITL:
Account {{account}} connected to a large number of new machines, which is unusual for this account.
These actions could indicate that the credentials of {{account}} have been abused for lateral movement.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.AGGREGATIVE_ICE.RECOMME: Assess the potential damage and look for IOC:
Review the accounts that have active sessions on the target machines
Review the credentials stored on the target machines
Look for other attack indications on the target machines
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.SUBTITLE_SIN: Service account {{account}} interactively logged on to {{target}} machine.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.SUBTITLE_MUL: Service account {{account}} interactively logged on to {{numOfMachines}} machines.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.RECOMMENDATI: Separate between using your service accounts and human accounts.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.GOLDEN_TICKET.SUBTITLE:
A Golden Ticket attack was detected in domain {{domain}}. The attacker used a forged Kerberos ticket for account {{account}} on machine {{target}}.
This ticket originated from machine {{source}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.GOLDEN_TICKET.RECOMMEND: An attacker has compromised your domain. Carefully investigate your environment and take action to contain the attacker.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.IRREGULAR_HOUR_USER.SUB:
Vault user {{user}} retrieved the password of privileged user {{account}} on machine {{target}} at {{startTime}}.
This action was flagged as a security event because {{user}} normally does not connect at this time.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.IRREGULAR_HOUR_USER.REC: Review this Vault userâs activities and ensure that they are valid.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.MALICIOUS_RETRIEVAL.SUB:
A potentially malicious retrieval of credentials from domain controller {{target}}, was detected on machine {{source}}.
The credentials retrieval was conducted by a successful domain controller replication.

Multiple potentially malicious retrievals of credentials were detected on machine {{source}}.
The credentials retrieval was conducted by a successful domain controller replication.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.MALICIOUS_RETRIEVAL.REC:
A Domain controller replication request (DCSync) must be initiated only by domain controllers.
If another authentication or management service in your network also executes domain controller replication,
it is highly recommended to protect these services at the same level as domain controllers.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.OVER_PASS_THE_HASH.SUBT:
An Overpass the Hash attack was detected in domain {{domain}}, which originated from machine {{source}}.
The attack abuses the credentials of account {{account}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.OVER_PASS_THE_HASH.RECO: Password change request was initiated. An attacker has compromised your domain. Carefully investigate your environment and take action to contain the attacker.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.PAC_ATTACK.SUBTITLE:
A PAC Attack (MS14-068 exploitation) attempt was detected in domain {{domain}}, which originated from machine {{source}}.
The attacker attempted to elevate the privileges of account {{account}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.PAC_ATTACK.RECOMMENDATI: Make sure that Domain Controller {{target}} is updated with patch KB3011780.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.RISKY_COMMAND.SUBTITLE:
Suspicious session activities on {{target}} were detected in a privileged session.
The session was initiated by Vault user {{user}} with account {{account}} by executing {{command}} activity.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.RISKY_COMMAND.RECOMMEND: Review each security event associated with the session and its activities, and evaluate whether a response is required, such as live monitoring or manual termination of the in-progress session.
Review each security event associated with the session and assess its risk using the session's activities and recording. This session has already been disconnected.

Session suspension request was initiated. Review each security event associated with the session and its activities, and evaluate whether an additional response is required, such as manual resumption or termination of the suspended session.
A session termination request was initiated. Review each security event associated with the session and its activities, and evaluate whether an additional response is required.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.SUBTITLE_SINGLE_MAC: Privileged account {{account}} accessed {{target}} machine with a password that was not retrieved from CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.SUBTITLE_MULTI_MACH: Privileged account {{account}} accessed {{numOfMachines}} machines with a password that was not retrieved from CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.RECOMMENDATION_NO_R: Consider changing the passwords that were used without being retrieved.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.RECOMMENDATION_REME: Password change request was initiated. Ensure that your organizational policy and PAS controls are not bypassed, and that your managed accounts are controlled.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SPC.SUBTITLE: Privileged account {{account}} password was changed outside of CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SPC.RECOMMENDATION_NO_R: Consider reconciling the password of the account that was changed outside of CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SPC.RECOMMENDATION_RECO: Password reconciliation request was initiated. Ensure that your organizational policy and PAS controls are not bypassed, and take control over the managed accounts.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.SUBTITLE_SING: Privileged account {{account}} was used to access {{target}}, although this account is not managed in CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.SUBTITLE_MULT: Privileged account {{account}} was used to access {{numOfMachines}} machines, although this account is not managed in CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.RECOMMENDATIO: Consider onboarding the unmanaged privileged account to CyberArk PAS.

Onboard the newly discovered account, and assign the appropriate platform to securely manage the account. Discovered accounts that are filtered by an automatic onboarding rule do not require manual action.

This action was flagged as a security event because {{user}} does not normally access the Vault from this IP.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.VAULT_IRREGULAR_IP.RECO: Review this Vault userâs activities and ensure that they are valid.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.CLEARTEXT.SUBTITLE: Accounts credentials sent from {{source}} using LDAP simple bind were exposed in clear-text.
